@startuml
title Viaverse Notification / Inbox / Delivery — Class Model

class Notification {
  id: NotificationId
  accountId: AccountId
  type: NotificationType
  priority: Priority
  title: String
  body: String
  deepLink: String?
  status: NotificationStatus
  deduplicationKey: String
  createdAt: Instant
}

class NotificationAttempt {
  id: UUID
  notificationId: NotificationId
  channel: PUSH | EMAIL | SMS
  provider: String
  status: AttemptStatus
  attemptNo: Int
  errorCode: String?
  sentAt: Instant?
}

class NotificationPreference {
  accountId: AccountId
  notificationType: String
  pushEnabled: Boolean
  emailEnabled: Boolean
  smsEnabled: Boolean
  quietHours: QuietHours?
  digestMode: DigestMode
}

class DeviceToken {
  id: UUID
  accountId: AccountId
  platform: IOS | ANDROID | WEB
  tokenHash: String
  status: DeviceStatus
  lastSeenAt: Instant
}

class NotificationTemplate {
  type: NotificationType
  locale: Locale
  titleTemplate: String
  bodyTemplate: String
  channelOverrides: Json
  version: Int
}

class NotificationPolicy {
  shouldNotify()
  selectChannels()
  respectQuietHours()
  rateLimit()
  shouldDigest()
  shouldRetry()
}

class AdminCampaign {
  id: UUID
  segmentRule: String
  templateId: String
  status: CampaignStatus
  rateLimitPerMinute: Int
  createdBy: AccountId
}

class NotificationEvents {
  NotificationCreated
  NotificationSent
  NotificationFailed
  NotificationRead
  CampaignStarted
  CampaignCompleted
}

Notification "1" o-- "*" NotificationAttempt
NotificationPreference ..> Notification : controls
DeviceToken ..> NotificationAttempt : used for push
NotificationTemplate ..> Notification : renders
NotificationPolicy --> NotificationPreference : uses
NotificationPolicy ..> Notification : validates
AdminCampaign ..> Notification : creates many
Notification ..> NotificationEvents : emits
NotificationAttempt ..> NotificationEvents : emits
AdminCampaign ..> NotificationEvents : emits

note bottom
Store tokenHash/display metadata, not raw device tokens in broad read models.
Raw provider token access should be restricted/encrypted.
end note
@enduml
